Prof. James B. Kuo's Home Page

NTUEE 臺大電機 ■ ■ ■ ■ ■

                                                                                                               
█ 歡迎光臨 Welcome!      █ Professor
James B. Kuo █ 郭正邦教授  █ IEEE Fellow       

 
 

■Prof. James B. Kuo
received a BSEE degree from National Taiwan University, Taipei, Taiwan in 1977, an MSEE degree from Ohio
State University, Columbus, Ohio, USA in 1978,and a PhDEE degree from Stanford University, Stanford, California, USA in 1985. After the
PhD program, he worked as a research associate in IC Lab of Stanford University before
joining National Taiwan University as an associate professor in 1987. He became a
professor at NTU in 1990. Between 2000 and 2002, while on leave from NTUEE, he has been with University of Waterloo,
Ontario, Canada as a professor. In 2001, he was
granted the prestigious Canada Research Chair Professor on low-voltage CMOS VLSI by Canadian
government. In 2006, he was granted the prestigious Life Distinguished Professor by NTU. His research expertise is in the field of low-voltage CMOS VLSI circuits
and SPICE compact modeling of deep-submicron bulk and SOI CMOS and BiCMOS VLSI devices. He
became an IEEE fellow in 1999 for contributions to modeling CMOS VLSI devices.  He
has been granted  the Outstanding Research Award in Microelectronics three
times,
by National Science Council 1995, 2000, and 2003. He served
as an AdCom member and the VP of membership for the IEEE Electron Devices Society. He is a
distinguished lecturer of the IEEE Electron Devices Society. He has published over 320 technical papers and authored eight books including Low-Voltage SOI
CMOS VLSI Devices and Circuits (John Wiley, New York, 2001), Low-Voltage CMOS VLSI
Circuits (John Wiley: New York, 1999) and CMOS VLSI Engineering Silicon-On-Insulator (SOI)
---Kluwer Boston, 1998. He has graduated 100 MS and PhD students specialized in CMOS
circuit design and device modeling, currently working in leading US and Taiwan's
microelectronics companies.                  　       











█ 郭正邦教授
1977年臺大電機畢業, 1978年美國俄亥俄州立大學電機碩士,1985年美國史坦福大學電機博士. 1987年返回母校成電機系副教授. 1990年成為臺大教授.
2000-2002年臺大留職停薪,於加拿大滑鐵盧大學任職正教授. 2001年獲得加拿大政府所頒發的微電子講座教授. 郭教授研究專長在低電壓超大型積體電路設計及深次微米CMOS
SPICE精簡元件模型.郭教授於1999年由對CMOS超大型機電CMOS元件模型的傑出貢獻成為IEEE fellow (國際電子電機學會院士).
郭教授是臺大微電子領域第一位獲得IEEE fellow榮譽的教授. 郭教授也是在電子元件領域以在台灣本土努力成果因而獲得IEEE
fellow榮譽之全國第三位教授.郭教授在1995及2000及2003年曾三度獲得國科會所頒發微電子研究傑出獎. 2006年獲得臺大特聘教授的榮譽. 郭教授熱心於國際IEEE 電子元件學會活動, 曾任IEEE電子元件學會理事及會員部副總.郭教授是IEEE電子元件學會傑出演講者.郭教授著作320篇技術論文及九本教科書,包括於紐約Wiley出版的近作:低電壓CMOS超大型積體電路(1999)及SOI(2001). 郭教授已指導100位專精於CMOS電路設計及元件模型博士碩士畢業學生, 任職於國內外著名微電子公司, 從事尖端研發工作. 　    ■ Teaching Diversified CMOS 多元金氧半積電技術 in 2008 and Digital IC in 2005



   

 



■ 2008 Outstanding Researcher Project from National Science Council■ 2007 IEEE Electron Devices Society Distinguished Lecturer ■  2006 Life Distinguished Professor Award of National Taiwan University■  2005 IEEE Electron Devices Society AdCom Member■ 2004 IEEE Electron Devices Society VP of Membership■ 2003 Outstanding
